cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is about pedestrian detection using a combination of traditional handcrafted features and convolutional neural networks. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a new framework for integrating features from multiple layers of a CNN, which involves machine learning techniques such as AdaBoost, suggesting that it could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of deep learning techniques, which could further support its classification under cs.NE (neural and evolutionary computing). Finally, the experiments involve the use of various datasets, indicating that the paper could also be relevant to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
